{"word":"ἀπειλή","slug":"ἀπειλή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπειλή</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> uncertain\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>mostly in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <i>boastful promises, boasts</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in bad sense, <i>threats</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—in sg. <i>a threat of punishment</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b> <p/></div>"}]}